cu500_lin | 1 | 47 folios with 5 lines each in Arabic.  Folios 45b and 46a have 3 lines each in Arabic.
cu500_pal | 1 | The title page, folio 2a, is a palimpsest, done over 6-8 lines of fine script in several hands.  The script is only partly visible, but enough can be read to show that the notations are similarto those that appear on many books of juz&apos; title pages of Qur&apos;ans donated to mosques.  These, in addition to stating the waqf, usually include the incipit and the name of the copyist and sometimes the date of the work, the signatures of 1 or 2 witnesses, and some pious phrases.  The outer margin has a notation in general manuscript hand.  The manuscript is written in a fully pointed and fully voweled naskhi, all in the same black ink.  The title page and the surah titles are in thuluth khafif, the former in white, the latter in gold.  The manuscript is, on the whole, carefully executed, though mistakes are not wanting.  Where these occur a correction has frequently been attempted in a different hand by erasing and rewriting, with the result that the line or page is disfigured.  Reading symbols and notations are lacking.  Folios 45b and 46a contain a naskhi script, each irregularly outlined in black.
